Patient Needs: 20yo female IVC from home with family and hx of depression. Superficially cut her L arm and neck with a knife. Pseudoseizures up to 6-7x a day. Currently in ICU on LOA.
Care Recommendations: Pt will be free of SI. Pt will demonstrate an alleviation of depressive sxs and that depressive sxs do not impair daily functioning. Pt will complete a written safety plan. Pt will demonstrate an improved stability and identify 3 ways to maintain stable mood and behavior for 3 consecutive days. Pt will cooperate with tx and be compliant with med regime. Pt will be monitored for medication tolerance and compliance. Pt will eat at least 50% of meals and sleep at least 6hrs nightly. Attend groups daily and build coping skills. Fall risk safety will be monitored daily. Pt will receive education and support. Pt will review plan of care initially and weekly.
